Product Description

Simple Modern Legacy Backpack

The Legacy is the newest addition to Simple Modern's exclusive backpack collection! This stylish backpack is ideal for school, work, traveling, and everyday use for men, women and kids. It features a padded laptop sleeve, tablet sleeve, small pockets for pens and USBs, a zip-closure mesh pocket, two exterior zip-closure pockets, padded adjustable straps and a travel strap. In addition, the Legacy includes two water bottle sleeves. Pick your favorite color and enjoy the Legacy on your everyday adventures!

Rolling Suitcase Strap

Travel with ease when you carry your Legacy Backpack. The bag includes a strap on the back which allows you to connect your backpack to your rolling suitcase.

Padded Laptop and iPad Compartment

Inside the main compartment, you will find a separate padded compartment for your laptop (up to 15") or tablet. Whether you are studying at a coffee shop, working at the office, or going through the airport security line, this allows for convenient access and protection for your tech. Along with the technology sleeve, there are several pockets within the backpack to sort your accessories.

Dual Water Bottle Sleeves

With two water bottle sleeves, you can stay hydrated on the go. Whether you are at school, traveling, or on a big adventure - you can easily carry your Simple Modern drinkware (up to 22oz bottle sizes).

Professional Grade Water Resistant Fabric

This Legacy is made for the adventure of every day life and more. The bag is made of water resistant 600 D Polyester fabric and has reinforced stitching for durability.

How does Amazon calculate star ratings?
Amazon calculates a products star ratings based on a machine learned model instead of a raw data average. The model takes into account factors including the age of a rating, whether the ratings are from verified purchasers, and factors that establish reviewer trustworthiness.

Measures about 18 H x 12 W x 6 D (4 top depth)

Pros:
-Size
-Weight
-Number of zip internal and external sections
-Fabric feel, quality, and color accuracy
-Comfortable straps and top handle
-Well worth the [regular] price
-Excellent craftsmanship
-Not too deep to be bulky
-Simplistic exterior design
-Exterior zip sections pretty easy to open one-handed

Cons (all relatively minor):
-Laptop strap relatively useless at securing in place smaller laptops
-When fully/over packed, the bottom of your laptop pokes you in the back a bit. But, I wear backpacks fairly tight/close to my body.
-Main compartment not lockable
-Chest strap can be uncomfortable for women with above B-size cups

5.0 out of 5 stars Great Backpack
Reviewed in the United States on December 14, 2019
Size: 25 Liter LegacyColor: -RiptideVerified Purchase
I live in the PNW so it rains... quite a lot. I was looking for a waterproof bag, and honestly they were all wayyyyy out of my price range. I love the color teal so when this backpack showed up in my search I thought Id give it a shot.

Its not waterproof, but I bought a waterproof cover on amazon for about $9 that fits perfect.

The bag itself feels sturdy and well made, it has loops on the straps for a clip and a LUGGAGE strap which I wasnt expecting but was a great surprise.

Overall Im really happy. It fits everything I need for work (lunch, notebook, pencil case) plus plenty of room for study/personal items (more notebooks, a thick textbook, raincover, medicine)

Im really impressed with the quality for the price so far. Ill update this post if anything changes.

IF I did have to critique anything, Id say it would be nice to have a padded bottom to the bag.

Mari P.
3.0 out of 5 stars Cute but not very functional.
Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2019
Size: 25 Liter LegacyColor: -SlateVerified Purchase
I recently purchased two backpacks in different colors for a vacation, one for me and one for my spouse, I thought the price was great. Now my review with the good points first: the bag is roomy and the canvas is stiff/sturdy. Also it looks great, the color of the fabric is very attractive and looks higher end overall. The bad: The zippers were a nightmare to open/close, I think since the zippers have a fabric lip over them for aesthetic purposes they impede their actual function. The inside compartments are virtually useless, they are too small and they are in the back of the pack, so they are hard to get to. The side pockets are too small, they can't hold a regular water bottle much less a metal one and this was due partly to the size of the pocket as well as the stiffness of the fabric. Lastly, the straps were painful and hard, I ended up with welts over my clavicles, the chest strap was awkward as well, it was hard to open/close. I would recommend these backpacks if you are only going to put smaller and very light items inside.

5.0 out of 5 stars Awesome Backpack for a Killer Price
Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2019
Size: 25 Liter LegacyColor: -Midnight BlackVerified Purchase
I needed a new day-to-day backpack after the zippers broke on the one I bought last year (Mancro brand).
So far, this bag seems to be a perfect replacement and way better quality!

I love its all-black, low profile and slim design looks cool and allows for more capacity then it appeared to have in the pictures. It's equipped with all the smaller pockets you might want in addition to the main pouch.
-Two on the front with covered zippers that span the width of the bag.
-And two inside: One mesh towards the top on the opening side and another, covered, towards the bottom against the laptop pouch.
-The laptop pouch Snuggly fits my 15in MacBook pro and a thin folder for documents.
-And there are spots for pens/sharpies, etc. near the bottom of the bag against your back. (Placement of these might be a little odd to some, but for the most part, won't get in the way.

This bag is awesome for everyday work use, and could also be used for school or short trips with enough room for binders or clothes!
I would buy again, especially at the current price!

Andrea
5.0 out of 5 stars This backpack does not disappoint!
Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2020
Size: 25 Liter LegacyColor: -LilacVerified Purchase
I ordered this backpack for my second college semester and I was not disappointed! First off, I love the color, it is a slightly darker purple than the photo but I do not mind it and I think its super cute. The straps are super comfortable and dont dig into your shoulders because they are padded. And although I do not use the chest strap it is a nice feature and does not bother me when I have the bag on. It is super big inside, which is amazing because when its on the backpack does not look huge or bulky. I can fit a multi subject notebook, folder, planner, pencil case and my laptop too in the main compartment. One issue I did have is that my laptop already is in a case and when I tried to slip it into the strapped laptop compartment it does not fit. But I do not mind because I just store folders in there instead and the laptop fits nicely in the big compartment. Its super lightweight, I dont feel like i am even carrying that much stuff! The water bottle sleeve fits my 16 oz bottle and I even tried a 20 oz one and it fit perfectly as well. I also really love the little pockets and zippers because theyre great for tiny things like a calculator or an ID or tissues and you avoid having to dig around for them. Overall I really recommend this bag, its cute, comes in lots of colors, really comfy and super affordable.
